    <h1>Welcome to the Puppy Training Guide</h1>
    <p>This guide is your go-to resource for understanding and implementing effective training techniques for your puppy, ensuring a happy, healthy, and well-behaved canine companion.</p>

    <!-- Introduction to Puppy Training -->
    <h2>1. Introduction to Puppy Training</h2>
    <p>Early training is crucial for puppies to ensure they learn essential behaviors and commands. This section covers the basics of getting started with puppy training, emphasizing the importance of patience and consistency.</p>

    <!-- Preparing Your Home -->
    <h2>2. Preparing Your Home</h2>
    <p>Before bringing your puppy home, it's important to puppy-proof your living space to prevent accidents and ensure your pet's safety. Remove hazardous items, secure loose wires, and set up a comfortable sleeping area.</p>

    <!-- Potty Training -->
    <h2>3. Potty Training</h2>
    <p>Potty training is a fundamental aspect of puppy care. Establish a routine by taking your puppy outside at regular intervals, especially after meals and naps. Reward successful potty breaks with praise and treats to reinforce positive behavior.</p>

    <!-- Socialization -->
    <h2>4. Socialization</h2>
    <p>Socializing your puppy with other dogs and humans is key to developing a well-adjusted adult dog. Gradually introduce your puppy to new experiences, ensuring positive and controlled interactions.</p>

    <!-- Basic Commands and Obedience -->
    <h2>5. Basic Commands and Obedience</h2>
    <p>Teach your puppy basic commands such as "sit," "stay," "come," and "heel" to build a foundation for good behavior. Use positive reinforcement techniques, such as treats and praise, to encourage compliance.</p>

    <!-- Addressing here a placeholder for Behavioral Issues, Advanced Training Techniques, and more -->

    <h2>9. Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Q: How long does it take to potty train a puppy?</strong></li>
        <p>A: The time it takes to potty train a puppy can vary, but with consistent training, most puppies can learn within a few weeks to a few months.</p>
        <li><strong>Q: What do I do if my puppy is afraid of other dogs?</strong></li>
        <p>A: Gradual exposure to other dogs in controlled, positive environments can help alleviate fear. Consider puppy socialization classes as a safe way to introduce your puppy to other dogs.</p>
    </ul>

